exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib glossary lookup matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib glossary lookup <term> [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Resolve a Finnish/colloquial term or synonym to its definition + related commands (DB-backed). Exit 5 if undefined — the miss is recorded for the groomer.
  Auth: requires login (any authenticated user).

ARGUMENTS
  <term> STRING    A word or synonym, e.g. pumppari (required)

FLAGS
  (none)

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  single term: { term, synonyms[], definition, relatedCommands:[{command,summary}], relatedEntity } | batch (a,b,c): ListEnvelope<{ term, found, entry }>

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 5 (HTTP 404)  No entry for the term  → Try \`ib glossary list --search <term>\`; the miss is queued for definition
  exit 2  Not authenticated      → Run \`ib auth login\`

NOTES
  - Comma-separated terms (a,b,c) run a batch lookup returning a ListEnvelope of {term,found,entry}; a single term keeps the single-entry shape.

EXAMPLES
  ib glossary lookup pumppari
  ib glossary lookup betoniasema
  ib glossary lookup loma,saikku,pyhä
"
`;

