exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib vehicle driver-assign matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib vehicle driver-assign <vehicleId> [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Assign a per-day driver to a vehicle (vehicleDriverDays). POST /api/vehicle/driverDays/save.
  Permissions: requires auth.page.vehicle.edit.
  Timezone: dates interpreted in active company timezone (Europe/Helsinki).

ARGUMENTS
  <vehicleId> NUMBER    vehicleId (required)

FLAGS
  --person NUMBER    Driver personId (required)
  --date DATE    Day YYYY-MM-DD or today/yesterday/tomorrow (default: today)

WRITE-SAFETY FLAGS
  --dry-run            Validate without persisting. Returns the would-be response.
  --idempotency-key K  Replay protection. Cached for 24h.
  --reason TEXT        Free-text justification. Stored in audit log.

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  raw backend response | { dryRun, wouldUpdate }

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 5 (HTTP 404)  Vehicle not found      → verify vehicleId
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Permission denied      → check auth.page.vehicle.edit
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

NOTES
  - personPvm-only: this sets just the day-driver bar and does NOT update the keikkat/palkit on the vehicle that day. For the atomic equivalent the grid uses, prefer \`ib driver assign\`.

SEE ALSO
  ib driver assign, ib driver gaps

EXAMPLES
  ib vehicle driver-assign 7 --person 555 --date 2026-06-02 --reason 'cover shift'
  ib vehicle driver-assign 7 --person 555 --dry-run
"
`;

